5. Geometry–Number Alchemy

Another strange bridge:

the Gauss circle problem.

Question:

How many integer lattice points lie inside a circle of radius r?

Area predicts:

\pi r^2

But counting lattice points gives:

discrete integer count

So geometry predicts number theory behavior.

Applications:
	•	crystallography
	•	signal processing
	•	coding theory.

